Subject: [PATCH] Use optimized Folia main dispatcher

Switch the Folia coroutine session to use OptimizedMainDispatcher instead of the tick-rate based MainDispatcher.

The optimized dispatcher no longer depends on mainDispatcherTickRateMs for repeatedly polling the queue. Instead, it can schedule work only when coroutine dispatches are actually submitted, avoiding unnecessary idle wakeups while still preserving single-threaded main dispatcher execution.

This reduces scheduler overhead for idle plugins and improves burst handling by letting the optimized dispatcher coalesce queued coroutine work instead of relying on fixed-rate draining.

